page.title: 09Housing,South Benfleet.
page.content: Most houses are privately-owned and have front and back gardens.Nearly all have at least one garage.New houses being built are predominately detached,but there is also a good number of semi-detached property as well as bungalows,many having been built in the Thirties.In the last decade purpose-built blocks of flats have made an appearance,particularly along the High Road as have rows of 'Town'or 'Link' Houses in small terraces near the station.Homes for elderly people who require special care are available.There is also such a home for young people.A small amount of rented Council accommodation is available,mostly in semi-detached cottage-style house.
